","Danmark":"Denmark","Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Holbæk, Denmark":"Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Holbæk, Denmark","Kallundborg, Holbæk, Denmark":"Kallundborg, Holbæk, Denmark","Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Ars, Holbæk, Danmark":"Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Ars, Holbæk, Denmark","Denmark":"Denmark","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Peder","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peder Strangesen was born as the son of Strange Ulfeldt and Ukendt. He had at least 1 son and 3 daughters with Ingeborg Esbernsdatter. He died in 1241, in Denmark."},"et":{"–1241":"–1241","–Male":"Surnud","–1267":"–1267","1200–1255":"1200–1255","1210–1252":"1210–1252","1228–1261":"1228–1261","–Female":"Surnud","1144–1186":"1144–1186","1186":"1186","1241":"1241","1252":"1252","1261":"1261","1228":"1228","about 1228":"umbes 1228","1169":"1169","1267":"1267","1255":"1255","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","1144":"1144","about 1200":"umbes 1200","Danmark":"Taani","Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Holbæk, Denmark":"Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Holbæk, Taani","Kallundborg, Holbæk, Denmark":"Kallundborg, Holbæk, Taani","Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Ars, Holbæk, Danmark":"Kalundborg, Vor Frue, Ars, Holbæk, Taani","Denmark":"Taani"},"fi"